pr_body:
This adds a basic wrapper for diffing multiple tables
expressed as json in the following form:

```js
{
  "names": ["sheet1", "sheet2"],
  "tables": {
    "sheet1": {
       "columns": ["col1", "col2", "col3"],
       "rows": [
           { "col1": 42, "col2": "x", "col3": null },
           { "col1": 24, "col2": "y", "col3": null },
           ...
       ]
    },
    "sheet2": {
       ...
    }
  }
}
```

Hi Rob,

As you can see from the commit comments:

> Corrected values for the ranges of signed Integer types to include the correct minimum value
> Added test case for minimum value of an integer with a restriction/range
> Added test case for 'min' alias value which is currently broken

I've included an example of a still broken case where if you specify a restriction that uses the 'min' keyword, it does not work.

leaf restricted-ueight-min-alias {
    type int8 {
        range "min..max";
    }
}

